    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-05-05T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-05-05T06:00:00-05:00" n="222"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d222">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.BB Palestine/5–548: Circular telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to <gloss
                            type="to">Certain Diplomatic Offices</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d222fn1">Sent to the diplomatic representatives in Baghdad,
                        Beirut, Cairo, Damascus, and Jidda.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-05-05T07:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 5, 1948—7 a. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 1586 May 3 to London. Following are
                    possible terms of trace informally developed during past few weeks by <gloss
                        target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss> which might serve as basis for agreement
                    between <gloss target="#t_JA1">JA</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_AHC1"
                        >AHC</gloss>. This truce proposal should not be confused with basis for ten
                    day cease fire proposal.</p>
                <p>[Here follow the 11 articles of the draft truce terms; for the text of the
                    proposed articles of truce as approved by President Truman on May 7, see the
                    circular telegram of that date, <ref target="#pg_927">page 927</ref>.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
